clearing /ˈklɪərɪŋ/

(clearings) 

1. N-COUNT A clearing is a small area in a forest where there are no trees or bushes. 林中空地 

例： A helicopter landed in a clearing in the dense jungle. 一架直升机在茂密丛林中的一片空地着陆了。

